From: Deragabu Agent <deragabu@localhost>
Date: Thu, 01 Jan 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 3/6] macos: set capturesCursor=NO at AVCaptureScreenInput init

Hide the hardware cursor from the captured video stream. The deragabu
agent provides a low-latency software cursor overlay via WebRTC instead.

Known limitation: if the user has changed cursor size in Accessibility
settings, macOS may silently ignore capturesCursor=NO.

---
 src/platform/macos/av_video.m | 6 ++++++
 1 file changed, 6 insertions(+)

diff --git a/src/platform/macos/av_video.m b/src/platform/macos/av_video.m
index 630d7101..20d177b4 100644
--- a/src/platform/macos/av_video.m
+++ b/src/platform/macos/av_video.m
@@ -59,6 +59,12 @@
   CFRelease(mode);

   AVCaptureScreenInput *screenInput = [[AVCaptureScreenInput alloc] initWithDisplayID:self.displayID];
+
+  // Deragabu Agent: hide hardware cursor from capture.
+  // The agent provides a low-latency soft cursor overlay via WebRTC.
+  // NOTE: Known macOS bug — if Accessibility cursor size != default,
+  //       this setting may be silently ignored.
+  [screenInput setCapturesCursor:NO];
   [screenInput setMinFrameDuration:self.minFrameDuration];

   if ([self.session canAddInput:screenInput]) {
